Feel free to ignore this, but wondering if we can simplify this a bit. Something along the lines of:
int originalTaskListSize = taskList.size()
taskList.removeAll(validTaskNamesSet)   // make sure the types are compatible to do this

// Only invalid tasks are left behind
taskList.forEach(taskName -> {
     orphanLockList.add(KeyBuilder.datastreamTaskLock(_cluster, connector, taskPrefix, taskName));
});

if  (taskList.size() == originalTaskListSize) {
    // None of the tasks are valid, thus we can safely remove the prefix node
    orphanLockList.add(KeyBuilder.datastreamTaskLockPrefix(_cluster, connector, taskPrefix));
}

